    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the onion and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato paste</strong>, most of the <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for a further 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>coconut stock</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until starting to thicken – this is your <strong>lighter Goan-style</strong> <strong>curry sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
